    "title": "Demystifying Tech - Episode 3: What is a Database?",
    "slug": "demystifying-tech-episode-3-what-is-a-database",
    "content": "<h2 id=\"\"><strong id=\"\">What is a Database?</strong></h2><p id=\"\">A database is an organized collection of structured information, or data, typically stored electronically in a computer system. It's one of the most essential aspects of software because at its core, an application is just a way for the user to input data (using forms and buttons) and then access data on a webpage. However, the creation of the importance of a thorough database structure is often overlooked in software development.</p><h2 id=\"\">‍<strong id=\"\">How do databases work?</strong></h2><p id=\"\">In this video from our <em id=\"\">Demystifying Tech </em>series, Airdev's co-founder Andrew Haller goes to the whiteboard to describe what a database is, why it's important, and how they work. All in simple terms.</p><h4 id=\"\">‍</h4><figure id=\"\" class=\"w-richtext-figure-type-video w-richtext-align-center\" style=\"padding-bottom:33.75%\" data-rt-type=\"video\" data-rt-align=\"center\" data-rt-max-height=\"33.75%\" data-rt-dimensions=\"0:0\"><div id=\"\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/jvVJek_lJ5E?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></div></figure><h3 id=\"\"><strong id=\"\">About our <em id=\"\">Demystifying Tech </em>series</strong></h3><p id=\"\">In this educational video series, we take a term from tech or software and explain what it means in very simple terms.</p><h3 id=\"\"><strong id=\"\">Watch all episodes from our Demystifying Tech series</strong></h3><ul id=\"\"><li id=\"\"><a href=\"https://www.airdev.co/post/demystifying-tech-episode-1-what-is-an-api\" target=\"_blank\">Episode 1: What is an API?</a><br></li></ul><ul id=\"\"><li id=\"\"><a id=\"\" href=\"https://www.airdev.co/post/demystifying-tech-episode-2-binary\" target=\"_blank\">Episode 2: Binary</a><br></li></ul><ul id=\"\"><li id=\"\">Episode 3: What is a Database?</li></ul>",
    "summary": "Andrew explains what databases really are at their core, how they're similar to Excel, and how to set one up based on Twitter as an example.",
    "featuredImage": "https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/62aa5d914f45160a7f155660/62aa5d924f451687f115585d_database2.svg",
    "imageAltText": "An illustration of a person pointing to a white board that says \"What is a Database?\"",
    "ogImage": "https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/62aa5d914f45160a7f155660/62aa5d924f45166df9155a54_database2.jpg",
